Summary

This report summarizes (in both code and text) the analysis carried out for âEfficacy of surgery and bronchoscopic resection in adult patients with resectable pulmonary typical carcinoid tumours: a systematic review.â All code is available online.1 http://www.github.com/joebrew/andresobeso

Data processing

Prior to analysis, data from the excel spreadsheet (data/Tabla excel analisis.xlsx) are read in and processed to a âtidyâ format (Wickham 2014Wickham, Hadley. 2014. âTidy Data.â The Journal of Statistical Software 59 (10). http://www.jstatsoft.org/v59/i10/.) using the script global.R.

Models

Are there statistically significant differences in the following outcome measures, as a function of the intervention type: Complete Resection, Residual Disease, Recurrence rate, Long tern successful rate and Survival

Methods for modeling

Simple ordinary least squares, weighted by N (sample size), and adjusted for Age, Sex, and months followed up. Formulaically:

<outcome> ~ (Group + `Age (yr)` + `Male (%)` + `Follow up (months)`) * `N`

The results are both tabular and graphical. In both, the âreferenceâ group is Surgery (ie, the value shown is for Bronchoscopy). A p-value of less than 0.05, or a chart with the vertical uncertainty line not crossing the 0 line, is considered statistically significant. For survival outcomes, follow up months was removed from the right hand side of the equation.

We use the below R code to generate a model and plot for each outcome variable.

# Define function for model
model <- function(outcome,
                  data){
  data$Group <- factor(data$Group, levels = c('Surgery', 'Bronchoscopy'))
  if(grepl('urvival', outcome)){
    the_formula <- paste0('`', outcome, '` ~ Group +',  '`Age (yr)` + `Male (%)`')
  } else {
    the_formula <- paste0('`', outcome, '` ~ Group +',  '`Age (yr)` + `Male (%)` + `Follow up (months)`')
  }
  
  the_formula <- as.formula(the_formula)
  fit <- lm(the_formula, weights = data$N, data = data)
  ci <- confint(fit)
  coefs <- coef(fit)
  out <-data.frame(coef = names(coefs), coefs, ci)
  out$coef <- gsub('Group', '', out$coef)
  row.names(out) <- NULL
  names(out) <- c('Variable', 'Coefficient', 'Lower', 'Upper')
  out$`P Value` <- summary(fit)$coefficients[,4]
  out_list <- list()
  out_list[[1]] <- out
  g <- ggplot(data = out %>%
                filter(Variable != '(Intercept)'),
              aes(x = Variable,
                  y = Coefficient)) +
    geom_point(color = 'red', alpha = 0.7) +
    geom_linerange(aes(x = Variable,
                       ymax = Upper,
                       ymin = Lower),
                   alpha = 0.7) +
    geom_hline(yintercept = 0, alpha = 0.7, lty = 2) +
    theme_databrew() +
    labs(title = '')
  out_list[[2]] <- g
  names(out_list) <- c('data', 'plot')
  return(out_list)
}
